1
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:06,880
Hey, isn't this a bit too close?

2
00:01:08,440 --> 00:01:09,840
Is everything alright?

3
00:01:10,560 --> 00:01:12,040
Everything is fine.

4
00:01:16,320 --> 00:01:18,640
When the distance becomes zero,

5
00:01:19,720 --> 00:01:21,800
the pupils dilate.

6
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:31,760
Heart rate noticeably increases.

7
00:01:34,480 --> 00:01:37,080
In conclusion, this scene actually works.

8
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:39,440
What do you mean it actually works?

9
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:41,840
You lunged at me like that.

10
00:01:42,160 --> 00:01:44,000
I'd be crazy not to be shocked.

11
00:01:48,520 --> 00:01:49,960
Excuse me, I'm going to the restroom.

12
00:01:57,640 --> 00:01:59,400
That touch just now...

13
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:03,400
In romance novels, it's sharing feelings.

14
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:07,280
But in biology, it's just heat transfer.

15
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:08,880
Right.

16
00:02:09,320 --> 00:02:10,520
It has to be like that.

17
00:02:24,480 --> 00:02:25,280
Ouch!

18
00:02:27,560 --> 00:02:28,760
Don't move.

19
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:34,240
There's broken glass everywhere.

20
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:39,600
Ms. Eris.

21
00:02:41,640 --> 00:02:43,880
You dress the wound for Ms. Eris.

22
00:02:45,120 --> 00:02:46,520
I'll sweep the floor.

23
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:55,080
Well...

24
00:02:56,480 --> 00:02:57,880
I was just going to pick it up.

25
00:02:58,840 --> 00:02:59,640
Does it hurt?

26
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:02,600
Just a little.

27
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:04,800
I'm sorry for breaking the glass.

28
00:03:10,760 --> 00:03:12,160
It's dangerous.

29
00:03:13,320 --> 00:03:14,920
Next time, don't clean it yourself.

30
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:19,240
Sorry.

31
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:32,600
Wound dressing scenes in novels happen

32
00:03:32,600 --> 00:03:36,280
so the protagonists can get closer.

33
00:03:37,760 --> 00:03:39,400
What are you talking about?

34
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:44,120
Don't tell me you broke the glass to simulate some crazy scene again!

35
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:45,160
No, I didn't.

36
00:03:46,160 --> 00:03:48,240
I accidentally broke it for real.

37
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:50,240
I really got cut.

38
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:51,040
But...

39
00:03:52,160 --> 00:03:53,480
just now...

40
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:57,720
I felt exactly what the character felt.

41
00:04:01,440 --> 00:04:03,400
Felt what the character felt?

42
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:09,160
And what did it feel like?

43
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:13,360
Well...

44
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:19,360
I don't know either.

45
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:35,720
Do you treat all your customers this well?

46
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:39,320
Next time you need something, call me.

47
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:42,880
Don't do it yourself, got it?

48
00:04:46,680 --> 00:04:47,480
Thank you.

49
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:54,560
You're okay now, right, Ms. Eris?

50
00:04:55,440 --> 00:04:56,280
I'm okay now.

51
00:04:57,120 --> 00:04:57,920
Alright.

52
00:05:02,440 --> 00:05:03,560
Claire.

53
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:05,160
Lock up the shop for me.

54
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:06,000
Something came up.

55
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,400
I have to go feed Tomo.

56
00:05:07,560 --> 00:05:08,360
I'm counting on you.

57
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:10,360
I'll be going now, Ms. Eris.

58
00:05:10,520 --> 00:05:11,320
See you later.

59
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:12,480
Don't forget.

60
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:14,960
She's always like this.

61
00:05:28,880 --> 00:05:31,840
How are you getting back?

62
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:33,480
I'm walking back.

63
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:36,880
Walk back? Seriously?

64
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:40,360
Yeah, my house is just in the alley behind.

65
00:05:42,160 --> 00:05:42,960
Hey!

66
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:44,800
Really?

67
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:46,080
Yeah.

68
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:48,080
How come I've never seen you around?

69
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:52,720
Not surprising. I like staying home.

70
00:05:53,080 --> 00:05:55,120
Reading books, writing novels all day.

71
00:05:55,960 --> 00:05:59,000
I don't like crowded places, it's chaotic.

72
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:01,160
I prefer peaceful environments.

73
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:03,000
No wonder.

74
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:06,120
No wonder I don't have a partner, right?

75
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:08,840
You're right about that.

76
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:11,240
I guess I'm used to being alone.

77
00:06:13,320 --> 00:06:15,400
My parents passed away when I was young.

78
00:06:16,440 --> 00:06:18,680
So I had to live with my grandma in Bangkok.

79
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:21,960
In high school, my grandma passed away too.

80
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:24,560
So I got used to being alone.

81
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:27,040
But I like it. It's peaceful.

82
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:31,960
I can walk back by myself.

83
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:33,080
You don't have to walk me.

84
00:06:33,080 --> 00:06:34,200
My house is really close.

85
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:39,040
It's fine, listening to you is fun.

86
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:42,720
Come on, it's just close by.

87
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:44,320
In case you have errands.

88
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:47,960
See?

89
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:51,440
Hello Cher, what's up?

90
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:54,320
Where are you and who are you with?

91
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:57,720
What is it? That's none of your business.

92
00:06:57,720 --> 00:07:00,280
Help me out. Tomo...

93
00:07:00,280 --> 00:07:02,280
hasn't finished his mission yet.

94
00:07:02,520 --> 00:07:04,080
And Uncle Noom just called me.

95
00:07:04,080 --> 00:07:05,920
He wants me to keep Praewa company.

96
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:08,160
Please go keep Praewa company for me.

97
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:10,560
Right now! That's all, bye-bye.

98
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:12,480
Hey! Cher!

99
00:07:15,520 --> 00:07:17,200
Always double-booking jobs.

100
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:21,000
You should hurry. I can walk back myself.

101
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,160
It's really close.

102
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:26,120
I'll get going then.

103
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:29,000
I'll use your services again next time.

104
00:08:25,640 --> 00:08:28,160
I felt exactly what the character felt.

105
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:53,240
[Meet me at the publisher's office tomorrow at 10 AM.]

106
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:45,200
Are you here to book another session?

107
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:52,240
It's completely ruined, Care.

108
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:57,080
The work I did.

109
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:02,920
I got comments saying it's so terrible.

110
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:07,480
Just the same old repetitive plots.

111
00:10:08,520 --> 00:10:10,320
Can't even compete with the new kids.

112
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:14,240
They said I write romance like a heartless robot.

113
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:19,840
I don't know who to talk to.

114
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:22,760
I don't have anyone, Claire.

115
00:10:25,640 --> 00:10:26,680
Calm down first.

116
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:29,880
I tried to do my very best.

117
00:10:31,880 --> 00:10:33,880
Why did it turn out so bad?

118
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:45,280
I try to be as capable as others expect me to be.

119
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:51,000
I'm afraid that if one day I'm not good,

120
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:53,480
like how others want me to be...

121
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:56,400
Would anyone still stay by my side?

122
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:20,400
Just let it all out.

123
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:24,600
You don't have to be strong all the time.

124
00:11:43,040 --> 00:11:45,760
I'm sorry, your shirt is all wet.

125
00:11:46,800 --> 00:11:47,600
It's totally fine.

126
00:11:57,840 --> 00:12:02,440
Who said Writer Eris is a robot?

127
00:12:07,880 --> 00:12:10,960
Crying like a baby, completely human.

128
00:12:15,680 --> 00:12:22,000
Just kidding. See? You can smile now.

129
00:12:25,960 --> 00:12:26,760
Thanks, Claire.

130
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:33,360
The plaster came off.

131
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:36,760
I'll redress the wound for you.

132
00:12:44,320 --> 00:12:48,120
I don't know why whenever I feel down,

133
00:12:48,120 --> 00:12:52,480
the only place I can feel weak is right here with you.

134
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:19,200
Feeling better?

135
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:22,640
You look a bit more like a person now.

136
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:25,600
A bit better.

137
00:13:26,360 --> 00:13:27,560
Thank you, Claire.

138
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:31,040
I've never let myself be like this before.

139
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:37,160
Can I ask you something?

140
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:41,720
When you said you have no one to call...

141
00:13:42,680 --> 00:13:43,600
Is that true?

142
00:13:44,440 --> 00:13:47,240
A beautiful, successful person like you?

143
00:13:48,280 --> 00:13:50,760
I usually only build worlds in my novels.

144
00:13:50,760 --> 00:13:52,480
Until I forgot to build one in reality.

145
00:13:53,240 --> 00:13:55,040
So when problems arise,

146
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:57,440
I don't know who to call.

147
00:13:58,920 --> 00:14:00,480
Everyone only knows Eris

148
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:03,040
as the famous mystery novelist.

149
00:14:04,280 --> 00:14:07,680
But no one knows this crybaby Eris.

150
00:14:14,560 --> 00:14:16,080
Hand me your phone.

151
00:14:17,320 --> 00:14:18,400
What for?

152
00:14:30,960 --> 00:14:34,360
Here's my number, save it.

153
00:14:36,400 --> 00:14:37,840
From now on,

154
00:14:37,840 --> 00:14:40,360
you don't have to be afraid of having no one to call.

155
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:42,800
Because you have me now.

156
00:14:44,440 --> 00:14:45,600
Whether it's about work,

157
00:14:47,520 --> 00:14:48,640
messy problems,

158
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:52,160
or just wanting to talk about crazy stuff,

159
00:14:53,800 --> 00:14:55,960
you can call me 24/7.

160
00:14:57,600 --> 00:14:59,880
I'll be on standby just to answer your call.

161
00:15:01,880 --> 00:15:03,200
24 hours?

162
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:05,800
Are you charging extra for this?

163
00:15:07,720 --> 00:15:08,800
If it's this number,

164
00:15:11,720 --> 00:15:13,360
I'll give you a free lifetime pass.

165
00:16:17,920 --> 00:16:19,120
Here's my house.

166
00:16:19,800 --> 00:16:21,160
Thank you so much for today.

167
00:16:25,280 --> 00:16:26,360
I'll go inside now.

168
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:28,160
Text me when you arrive.

169
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:34,880
Is this you being worried?

170
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:44,800
Yeah.

171
00:16:56,080 --> 00:16:57,600
I'll text you when I get home.

172
00:17:11,880 --> 00:17:12,880
Why am I smiling?

173
00:17:13,360 --> 00:17:14,760
Is she just being concerned?

174
00:17:36,560 --> 00:17:37,960
Well, well.

175
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:41,000
You seem to be in a good mood, Claire.

176
00:17:49,920 --> 00:17:52,160
Did you just walk Ms. Eris home?

177
00:17:53,320 --> 00:17:53,960
Hey!

178
00:17:54,360 --> 00:17:55,560
How did you know?

179
00:17:57,360 --> 00:17:58,520
See?

180
00:17:59,360 --> 00:18:02,040
Is there anything I want to know that I won't find out?

181
00:18:03,640 --> 00:18:05,080
Actually, I was just guessing,

182
00:18:05,320 --> 00:18:07,720
but someone ended up exposing themselves.

183
00:18:09,800 --> 00:18:10,840
And so?

184
00:18:11,520 --> 00:18:14,400
What's going on between you and Ms. Eris?

185
00:18:15,560 --> 00:18:16,480
Give me that.

186
00:18:16,480 --> 00:18:18,280
Cher, it's nothing like that.

187
00:18:18,480 --> 00:18:21,840
Just doing my duty as a good employee.

188
00:18:21,840 --> 00:18:23,920
Walking a customer to a safe place.

189
00:18:24,560 --> 00:18:27,000
Oh, a "good employee."

190
00:18:28,480 --> 00:18:29,840
I don't think so.

191
00:18:32,760 --> 00:18:35,200
Earlier you said she was crazy.

192
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:37,520
Complaining about this and that.

193
00:18:38,160 --> 00:18:39,040
And now?

194
00:18:39,880 --> 00:18:41,360
Your favorite writer

195
00:18:42,480 --> 00:18:44,960
might just become your favorite person.

196
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:48,680
Favorite person? Nonsense.

197
00:18:49,800 --> 00:18:50,600
Spill it.

198
00:18:50,960 --> 00:18:52,040
Nothing at all.
